http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Kochi/Career-counselling-session-tomorrow/article14002169.ece

Gitam University in association with The Hindu School Edition will conduct a career counselling session for Intermediate students at Bharatiya Vidya Bhavan on T. D. Road here on January 18.It will start at 10.30 a.m. The session aims at creating awareness among Intermediate students on professional and general higher education courses, selection of engineering branches and institutes. The experts at the conference will also deal with how to choose the best engineering, pharmacy, or architecture colleges. Expert lectures on science and management programmes, opportunities, research and national-level tests will be delivered.The conference will also cover management education, especially at the undergraduate level.Details on opportunities for postgraduate management students will be given. A special question and answer session will also be held as part of the counselling session.Entry is free.